<title>INDIA: India's RBI has rupee &quot;under control&quot; - Chidambaram.</title>
<headline>India's RBI has rupee &quot;under control&quot; - Chidambaram.</headline>
<dateline>NEW DELHI 1997-05-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Indian Finance Minister P. Chidambaram said on Friday that he believes the rupee exchange rate is stable and the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) has the currency &quot;under control&quot;.</p>
<p>Chidambaram was asked if he thought the rupee was stable. &quot;I think so. I think the RBI has it under control,&quot; he told reporters after the lower house of parliament approved the 1997/98 (April-March) Finance Bill.</p>
